1
00:00:07,140 --> 00:00:10,010
♪

2
00:00:12,513 --> 00:00:15,348
Narrator: THIS SENIOR GENTLEMAN
SEEMS FAMILIAR.

3
00:00:15,448 --> 00:00:17,483
WE DEFINITELY KNOW
THAT UPRIGHT BEARING

4
00:00:17,518 --> 00:00:19,853
AND THAT SCAR.

5
00:00:19,920 --> 00:00:22,956
Man: IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU
AGAIN, SPEEDWAGON.

6
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:26,492
I UNDERSTAND YOU'RE
AN AMERICAN OIL TYCOON NOW.

7
00:00:26,527 --> 00:00:28,662
Speedwagon:
THAT'S A BIT EXAGGERATED.

8
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:31,698
YOU LOOK AS YOUNG AS EVER,
STRAIZO.

9
00:00:31,765 --> 00:00:34,801
HARD TO BELIEVE
WE'RE THE SAME AGE.

10
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:39,105
HAMON ENERGY IS LIFE ENERGY,
RIGHT? I ENVY YOU.

11
00:00:39,172 --> 00:00:40,206
♪

12
00:00:40,306 --> 00:00:42,275
Narrator: IT HAS BEEN
HALF A CENTURY

13
00:00:42,342 --> 00:00:45,311
SINCE JONATHAN JOESTAR
MADE HIS SACRIFICE.

14
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:47,881
STRAIZO HAS SUCCEEDED
MASTER TONPETTY,

15
00:00:47,948 --> 00:00:51,552
WHILE SPEEDWAGON HAS HAD SUCCESS
BUILDING A FORTUNE.

16
00:00:51,652 --> 00:00:55,488
TOGETHER, THEY'RE HEADED
FOR MEXICO TO SEE SOMETHING.

17
00:00:55,556 --> 00:00:57,691
THIS SOMETHING WAS DISCOVERED

18
00:00:57,724 --> 00:01:01,502
BY A SPEEDWAGON‐FUNDED
EXPLORATION TEAM.

19
00:01:01,568 --> 00:01:03,837
WHAT'S MORE
IS THAT IT'S A SECRET

20
00:01:03,904 --> 00:01:07,140
KNOWN ONLY
TO THESE SELECT FEW.

21
00:01:07,207 --> 00:01:11,712
Speedwagon: I TELL YOU, STRAIZO,
ONCE YOU LAY EYES ON THIS,

22
00:01:11,745 --> 00:01:15,549
I BELIEVE‐‐NO, I AM CERTAIN
YOU'LL FEEL A CHILL.

23
00:01:15,582 --> 00:01:16,883
IT'S FRIGHTFUL ENOUGH

24
00:01:16,917 --> 00:01:19,586
TO MAKE EVEN YOUR
DISCIPLINED HAIR STAND ON END.

25
00:01:19,686 --> 00:01:21,688
I FIND IT EVEN WORSE

26
00:01:21,755 --> 00:01:24,424
THAN THE TERROR
WE FACED 50 YEARS AGO

27
00:01:24,490 --> 00:01:26,426
WHEN WE ALL BATTLED WITH DIO.

28
00:01:26,492 --> 00:01:28,028
( Straizo gasps )

29
00:01:29,162 --> 00:01:32,933
I CAN'T BELIEVE
HOW LARGE THIS SPACE IS.

30
00:01:33,033 --> 00:01:35,669
Speedwagon: AND THIS IS
THE REASON WE CAME HERE.

31
00:01:35,736 --> 00:01:37,337
Straizo: WHAT? IT CAN'T BE!

32
00:01:37,403 --> 00:01:39,105
A STONE MASK!

33
00:01:39,172 --> 00:01:41,775
AND THERE ARE SO MANY OF THEM!

34
00:01:43,343 --> 00:01:44,444
( gasps )

35
00:01:51,785 --> 00:01:53,253
♪

36
00:01:53,286 --> 00:01:55,856
Man: IT WAS IN THE FALL OF 1938.

37
00:01:55,922 --> 00:01:58,525
I WAS DOING MY JOB,
JUST LIKE I ALWAYS DID,

38
00:01:58,592 --> 00:02:00,594
EYES PEELED FOR A MARK.

39
00:02:00,627 --> 00:02:02,468
Man #2: YOU GOTTA BE KIDDIN' ME.

40
00:02:02,536 --> 00:02:03,469
Man #1: HUH?

41
00:02:03,537 --> 00:02:04,638
Man #2: YOU REALLY NEVER HEARD

42
00:02:04,705 --> 00:02:06,272
OF THIS FINE BEVERAGE?

43
00:02:06,306 --> 00:02:09,943
ALL RIGHT. BY YOUR ACCENT,
I'D SAY YOU'RE IN FROM ENGLAND.

44
00:02:09,976 --> 00:02:11,477
TOURIST, HUH?

45
00:02:11,578 --> 00:02:13,379
( man #1 chuckles )

46
00:02:13,446 --> 00:02:14,648
Vendor: NO KIDDIN'?

47
00:02:14,748 --> 00:02:17,050
YOU'RE GONNA MAKE
THE BIG CITY YOUR HOME?

48
00:02:17,116 --> 00:02:18,552
WELL, IF YOU WANT A DRINK,

49
00:02:18,618 --> 00:02:20,887
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO LAY DOWN SOME SHEKELS.

50
00:02:20,954 --> 00:02:22,789
CASH IS THE KING AROUND HERE.

51
00:02:26,326 --> 00:02:27,761
THE NERVE OF HIM!

52
00:02:27,828 --> 00:02:30,263
YOU'RE NOT GONNA LET
THAT MOOK STEAL YOUR WALLET.

53
00:02:30,330 --> 00:02:31,264
GET AFTER HIM.

54
00:02:32,966 --> 00:02:33,834
Thief: HAH!

55
00:02:33,934 --> 00:02:36,402
WHAT A PATSY.
THAT WAS EASY AS PIE.

56
00:02:36,469 --> 00:02:38,605
‐ ( gasps )
‐ ( officer laughs )

57
00:02:38,672 --> 00:02:40,106
HEY‐A, SMOKEY.

58
00:02:40,173 --> 00:02:43,610
LOOKS LIKE I FINALLY CAUGHT YOU
RED‐HANDED, YA PUNK.

59
00:02:43,677 --> 00:02:45,311
( Smokey yells )

60
00:02:45,345 --> 00:02:48,515
Officer: WHAT ARE YA DOIN'
ON MY BEAT, YOU TRASH?

61
00:02:48,582 --> 00:02:50,150
( Smokey coughs )

62
00:02:51,251 --> 00:02:52,252
I'M GONNA MAKE SURE

63
00:02:52,318 --> 00:02:54,020
THEY LOCK YOU UP
FOR 20 YEARS.

64
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:56,189
Smokey: TAKE IT EASY.
PLEASE, SIR.

65
00:02:56,256 --> 00:02:57,824
I ONLY PINCHED A WALLET.

66
00:02:57,858 --> 00:03:01,535
Officer: I HATE BOTTOM FEEDERS
LIKE YOU PREYIN' ON THE PUBLIC.

67
00:03:01,635 --> 00:03:04,538
BUT SEE, I'M NICE.
I'LL DO YOU A SOLID.

68
00:03:04,605 --> 00:03:08,308
I'M GONNA LET YOU
BRING ME $20 EVERY WEEK,

69
00:03:08,374 --> 00:03:12,312
ALSO HALF
OF EVERYTHING YOU GLOM.

70
00:03:12,378 --> 00:03:13,313
Englishman: HULLO.

71
00:03:13,379 --> 00:03:14,314
Officer: HMM?

72
00:03:14,380 --> 00:03:15,716
♪

73
00:03:15,782 --> 00:03:18,685
HEY, IT'S THE PIGEON
WHAT GOT HIS WALLET LIFTED.

74
00:03:18,719 --> 00:03:21,655
THIS IS EVIDENCE,
SO I'M GONNA BE KEEPIN' IT.

75
00:03:21,722 --> 00:03:24,390
Englishman: WELL, NOW,
HOW SHALL I PUT THIS?

76
00:03:24,457 --> 00:03:26,392
HERE IS WHAT HAPPENED.

77
00:03:26,459 --> 00:03:28,061
THERE ACTUALLY IS NO CRIME

78
00:03:28,161 --> 00:03:30,564
SINCE THAT WALLET
WAS A GIFT, CONSTABLE.

79
00:03:30,664 --> 00:03:31,565
‐ Officer: HMM?
‐ Officer #2: HMM?

80
00:03:31,665 --> 00:03:32,633
Smokey: EH?

81
00:03:32,699 --> 00:03:34,167
( narrating )
FOR SOME REASON,

82
00:03:34,234 --> 00:03:36,737
THIS SIX‐AND‐A‐HALF‐FOOT
GIANT OF AN ENGLISHMAN

83
00:03:36,837 --> 00:03:39,172
WAS COVERING FOR ME.

84
00:03:39,239 --> 00:03:41,675
Englishman: SO THEN, SIR,

85
00:03:41,742 --> 00:03:44,545
WOULD YOU PLEASE RETURN
BOTH WALLET AND BOY?

86
00:03:44,578 --> 00:03:45,846
Officer: WHAT'D YOU JUST SAY?

87
00:03:45,912 --> 00:03:48,248
Englishman: AS I SAID,
IT WAS A GIFT.

88
00:03:48,314 --> 00:03:51,084
HE AND I ARE GOOD FRIENDS.

89
00:03:51,151 --> 00:03:53,854
LET HIM GO, PLEASE.

90
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:55,321
‐ ( Smokey grunts )
‐ Officer: UH‐HUH.

91
00:03:55,388 --> 00:03:58,258
A GOOD FRIEND, EH?

92
00:03:59,392 --> 00:04:00,701
WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME

93
00:04:00,767 --> 00:04:02,435
WHAT YOUR GOOD FRIEND'S NAME IS?

94
00:04:02,536 --> 00:04:03,770
Englishman: HMM...

95
00:04:03,837 --> 00:04:05,338
Officer:
WHAT'S THE MATTER, LIMEY?

96
00:04:05,405 --> 00:04:08,942
YOU WANT TO SEE WHAT
A NEW YORK POKEY IS LIKE? HUH?

97
00:04:09,042 --> 00:04:11,277
HERE'S A PRESENT FOR YOU.

98
00:04:13,747 --> 00:04:16,049
( officers laugh )

99
00:04:16,116 --> 00:04:17,383
( Smokey gasps )

100
00:04:17,450 --> 00:04:19,119
Englishman: THAT'S CURIOUS.

101
00:04:19,219 --> 00:04:22,956
HELP ME UNDERSTAND. WHY WOULD
YOU DO SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

102
00:04:23,023 --> 00:04:25,692
IT'S JUST
SUCH AN UNSAVORY THING TO DO.

103
00:04:25,759 --> 00:04:27,093
Officer: THERE IS NO REASON!

104
00:04:27,127 --> 00:04:30,764
I DO WHAT I LIKE WHENEVER
I FEEL LIKE IT, YOU FOOL!

105
00:04:30,797 --> 00:04:33,199
BUT IF SOMEONE WIPES
A BOOGER ON YOUR FACE,

106
00:04:33,266 --> 00:04:35,268
IT PROBABLY MEANS THAT‐‐

107
00:04:35,301 --> 00:04:38,271
Englishman: YOU'VE MADE
THE WRONG MOVE, YOU STUPID PIG!

108
00:04:39,806 --> 00:04:41,307
( Smokey gasps )

109
00:04:41,374 --> 00:04:42,743
( officer groaning )

110
00:04:42,809 --> 00:04:44,745
Officer #2: YOU WERE SHOT
RESISTING ARREST!

111
00:04:44,811 --> 00:04:45,746
( Englishman spits )

112
00:04:45,812 --> 00:04:47,380
PLEASE, TRY TO SHOOT ME,

113
00:04:47,447 --> 00:04:49,650
BUT I AM WARNING YOU RIGHT NOW,

114
00:04:49,716 --> 00:04:51,451
BEFORE YOU CAN PULL THE TRIGGER,

115
00:04:51,484 --> 00:04:54,921
I WILL HAVE BROKEN YOUR FINGER
LIKE A ROTTEN MATCHSTICK.

116
00:04:54,988 --> 00:04:56,557
Officer #2: NOT FROM OVER THERE!

117
00:04:56,623 --> 00:04:58,825
I'LL BLOW YOUR DAMN BRAINS OUT!

118
00:05:00,727 --> 00:05:03,504
Smokey: SUDDENLY HIS BODY
STARTED TO GIVE OFF

119
00:05:03,604 --> 00:05:05,672
SOME SORT OF GLOW.

120
00:05:08,441 --> 00:05:10,811
IT WAS JUST INCREDIBLE.

121
00:05:10,844 --> 00:05:13,780
THE SODA CAP BLEW OFF AND
FLEW AS FAST AS A BULLET

122
00:05:13,847 --> 00:05:16,617
STRAIGHT OVER
TO SNAP THE COP'S FINGER.

123
00:05:16,683 --> 00:05:18,619
( officer #2 screams )

124
00:05:18,685 --> 00:05:21,254
♪

125
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:22,756
( officers jabbering )

126
00:05:22,823 --> 00:05:25,859
( Englishman gasps )
I GAVE IN TO MY TEMPER AGAIN.

127
00:05:25,926 --> 00:05:28,128
CRAP. I'M IN FOR IT.

128
00:05:28,194 --> 00:05:30,631
OH, GRANNY ERINA'S
GOING TO BE FURIOUS.

129
00:05:30,697 --> 00:05:34,167
Smokey: HE BEAT DOWN TWO COPS,
BUT IS SCARED OF HIS GRANDMA?

130
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,869
Englishman: I'LL JUST EXPLAIN.

131
00:05:35,936 --> 00:05:39,272
GRANNY ERINA WILL UNDERSTAND
IF I EXPLAIN, WON'T SHE?

132
00:05:39,339 --> 00:05:40,340
ALL RIGHT. MR. PICKPOCKET,

133
00:05:40,373 --> 00:05:43,176
WHAT SAY WE HIGH‐TAIL IT
ON OUT OF HERE?

134
00:05:43,209 --> 00:05:44,778
♪

135
00:05:44,845 --> 00:05:46,212
Smokey: HE DIDN'T KNOW EXACTLY

136
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:48,982
HOW HE HAD LAUNCHED
THE BOTTLE CAP WITH SUCH FORCE.

137
00:05:49,049 --> 00:05:52,385
HE SAID HE COULD ALWAYS
DO THINGS LIKE THAT.

138
00:05:52,485 --> 00:05:56,022
APPARENTLY HIS GRANDPA COULD
DO THE SAME KIND OF THINGS,

139
00:05:56,056 --> 00:05:58,491
BUT HE DIED AT A YOUNG AGE.

140
00:05:58,559 --> 00:06:00,734
HIS DAD, WHO DIED IN THE WAR,

141
00:06:00,801 --> 00:06:02,803
DIDN'T HAVE
ANY TALENTS LIKE THAT.

142
00:06:02,869 --> 00:06:05,872
HIS MOM WAS GONE, TOO.

143
00:06:05,906 --> 00:06:07,674
I REALLY OWE YOU BIG TIME.

144
00:06:07,741 --> 00:06:09,075
EVERYONE CALLS ME SMOKEY,

145
00:06:09,142 --> 00:06:11,978
AND I'D SURE LIKE IT
IF YOU'D TELL ME YOUR NAME.

146
00:06:12,846 --> 00:06:14,581
JoJo: IT'S JOESTAR,

147
00:06:14,648 --> 00:06:17,017
JOSEPH JOESTAR.

148
00:06:17,083 --> 00:06:19,019
♪

149
00:06:25,559 --> 00:06:29,162
MY FRIENDS CALL ME JOJO.

150
00:06:32,866 --> 00:06:34,701
Straizo: WHAT IS THIS?

151
00:06:34,768 --> 00:06:37,771
WHO IS THAT A CARVING OF
ON THAT PILLAR?

152
00:06:37,871 --> 00:06:39,773
Speedwagon:
THAT'S NOT A CARVING.

153
00:06:39,873 --> 00:06:43,076
HE HAS AMINO ACIDS,
PROTEINS, AND CELLS,

154
00:06:43,109 --> 00:06:46,780
AND THOUGH IT'S FAINT,
HE HAS BODY HEAT AND A PULSE.

155
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:48,949
WE ARE LOOKING AT A LIVING MAN!

156
00:06:49,049 --> 00:06:50,617
( Straizo grunts )

157
00:06:50,684 --> 00:06:52,619
Speedwagon: STRAIZO, UNDERSTAND,

158
00:06:52,719 --> 00:06:55,622
WHO HE IS,
HOW LONG HE HAS BEEN THERE,

159
00:06:55,722 --> 00:06:58,191
HOW HE GOT THERE
IN THE FIRST PLACE,

160
00:06:58,258 --> 00:07:01,234
WHAT THE MASKS ARE FOR,
NONE OF THAT MATTERS.

161
00:07:01,301 --> 00:07:04,104
WE ARE HERE
FOR ONE PURPOSE ONLY.

162
00:07:04,137 --> 00:07:07,140
I BROUGHT YOU
BECAUSE OF YOUR HAMON ABILITY,

163
00:07:07,207 --> 00:07:09,976
SO YOU CAN USE IT
TO UTTERLY DESTROY HIM

164
00:07:10,076 --> 00:07:11,945
WHILE HE SLUMBERS IN THIS STONE.

165
00:07:11,978 --> 00:07:15,281
Straizo: AND JOSEPH JOESTAR?

166
00:07:15,315 --> 00:07:16,282
Speedwagon: WHAT?

167
00:07:16,316 --> 00:07:18,985
Straizo: JOSEPH JOESTAR,
HOW IS HE DOING?

168
00:07:19,052 --> 00:07:23,089
I HEAR HE HAS HAMON ABILITY
AND SAVED YOUR LIFE ONCE.

169
00:07:23,156 --> 00:07:26,159
Speedwagon:
WH‐WHY BRING UP JOJO NOW?

170
00:07:26,226 --> 00:07:30,897
Straizo: AS I RECALL, HE WAS
BUT 13 YEARS OF AGE AT THE TIME.

171
00:07:30,964 --> 00:07:32,999
YES, QUITE YOUNG.

172
00:07:33,066 --> 00:07:35,769
YOUR PLANE WAS
HIJACKED BY CRIMINALS

173
00:07:35,836 --> 00:07:38,004
WHO WANTED
TO HOLD YOU FOR RANSOM.

174
00:07:38,104 --> 00:07:41,007
( Speedwagon shuddering )

175
00:07:42,743 --> 00:07:46,346
Hijacker: HEY, KID, YOU CAN'T
STAY BACK HERE, YOU KNOW.

176
00:07:46,412 --> 00:07:47,914
GET UP FRONT!

177
00:07:50,350 --> 00:07:51,618
( JoJo sighs )

178
00:07:51,685 --> 00:07:53,019
YOU'RE HIJACKING THE PLANE

179
00:07:53,086 --> 00:07:55,121
AND KIDNAPPING SPEEDWAGON,
CORRECT?

180
00:07:55,188 --> 00:07:56,857
I AM ONLY A BYSTANDER.

181
00:07:56,923 --> 00:07:58,024
THIS IS HIS PROBLEM.

182
00:07:58,124 --> 00:08:00,126
I'M JUST GOING TO READ MY STORY.

183
00:08:00,193 --> 00:08:02,769
DO YOUR BUSINESS,
AND JUST LEAVE ME OUT OF IT.

184
00:08:02,836 --> 00:08:03,937
( Speedwagon gasps )

185
00:08:04,004 --> 00:08:05,205
Hijacker: WRONG ANSWER, PUNK!

186
00:08:05,271 --> 00:08:07,107
‐ NOW MOVE!
‐ Speedwagon: JOJO.

187
00:08:08,041 --> 00:08:10,210
( JoJo gasps )

188
00:08:12,546 --> 00:08:14,014
( growls )

189
00:08:14,047 --> 00:08:16,683
Speedwagon: NOT GOOD.

190
00:08:16,717 --> 00:08:18,719
THAT SUIT WAS A GIFT FROM ERINA.

191
00:08:18,785 --> 00:08:20,386
THIS'LL SET HIM OFF FOR SURE.

192
00:08:20,486 --> 00:08:22,523
HE'S GOT NO SENSE
OF SELF‐RESTRAINT.

193
00:08:22,556 --> 00:08:24,224
( JoJo growls )

194
00:08:24,290 --> 00:08:25,892
Speedwagon:
CONTROL YOURSELF, JOJO!

195
00:08:25,959 --> 00:08:27,227
JoJo: YOU FELLOWS DID KNOW

196
00:08:27,293 --> 00:08:29,062
THERE WAS
THE POSSIBILITY OF A CRASH

197
00:08:29,129 --> 00:08:31,497
IF YOU HIJACKED THIS PLANE,
DID YOU NOT?

198
00:08:32,566 --> 00:08:33,634
( pilot gasps )

199
00:08:35,536 --> 00:08:36,469
( Speedwagon gasps )

200
00:08:36,537 --> 00:08:38,839
IS THAT HAMON? OH, NO.

201
00:08:38,905 --> 00:08:41,542
♪

202
00:08:41,575 --> 00:08:42,976
( hijackers scream )

203
00:08:43,043 --> 00:08:44,845
Hijacker: WHAT DID
THAT CRAZY KID DO?!

204
00:08:44,911 --> 00:08:45,846
WE'RE GONNA CRASH!

205
00:08:45,912 --> 00:08:47,080
Hijacker #2: GRAB THE CONTROLS!

206
00:08:47,180 --> 00:08:49,149
Hijacker #3:
I CAN'T FLY, IDIOT.

207
00:08:49,215 --> 00:08:51,017
JoJo: HERE. GET THE PILOT READY.

208
00:08:51,084 --> 00:08:52,418
WE'RE GOING TO JUMP.

209
00:08:55,756 --> 00:08:57,524
( explosion )

210
00:08:57,591 --> 00:08:58,925
( both groan )

211
00:08:59,025 --> 00:09:02,102
Speedwagon: WHY CAN'T YOU EVER
JUST THINK THINGS THROUGH, JOJO?

212
00:09:02,168 --> 00:09:04,771
JoJo: I DO IN FACT,
A GREAT DEAL,

213
00:09:04,838 --> 00:09:09,442
MOSTLY ABOUT HOW TO BEST KEEP
YOU AND GRANNY ERINA SAFE.

214
00:09:11,111 --> 00:09:14,515
YOU TWO ARE
THE ONLY FAMILY THAT I'VE GOT.

215
00:09:14,581 --> 00:09:17,117
Speedwagon: HE MAY HAVE
HIS GRANDFATHER'S FACE,

216
00:09:17,183 --> 00:09:20,286
BUT HE'S FAR
FROM BEING A GENTLEMAN.

217
00:09:21,421 --> 00:09:23,790
THAT WAS THE DAY I DISCOVERED

218
00:09:23,857 --> 00:09:26,059
THAT JOSEPH
WAS ABLE TO USE HAMON.

219
00:09:26,126 --> 00:09:28,428
Straizo:
SO YOUNG JOSEPH INHERITED

220
00:09:28,461 --> 00:09:32,132
THE ABILITY TO CONTROL HAMON
FROM HIS GRANDFATHER JONATHAN?

221
00:09:32,198 --> 00:09:35,969
Speedwagon: YES, BUT WHY
ARE YOU SPEAKING OF HIM NOW?

222
00:09:36,036 --> 00:09:37,437
( whoosh )

223
00:09:39,740 --> 00:09:41,207
Speedwagon: WHAT THE HELL?!

224
00:09:41,274 --> 00:09:44,645
Straizo: I JUST TOOK
THE LIVES OF ALL THESE MEN,

225
00:09:44,745 --> 00:09:46,479
AND WHEN YOU LOSE YOUR LIFE,

226
00:09:46,547 --> 00:09:50,917
JONATHAN'S GRANDSON WILL KNOW
GRIEF AND ANGER AND HATE.

227
00:09:50,984 --> 00:09:53,987
HE WILL DEVELOP
A TREMENDOUS HATRED FOR ME.

228
00:09:54,054 --> 00:09:55,789
Speedwagon: NO! STRAIZO!

229
00:09:55,822 --> 00:09:58,324
♪

230
00:10:12,045 --> 00:10:14,380
( squelching )

231
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:16,382
( footsteps )

232
00:10:18,118 --> 00:10:19,352
Speedwagon: STRAIZO...

233
00:10:20,754 --> 00:10:23,023
HAVE YOU LOST YOUR SENSES?

234
00:10:23,089 --> 00:10:24,224
Straizo: I HAVEN'T.

235
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:26,459
IN FACT, MY THINKING
IS EXTREMELY CLEAR.

236
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:32,065
I CHOSE HAMON TO FORGE MY BODY
INTO SOMETHING PURE AND STRONG,

237
00:10:32,132 --> 00:10:35,068
BUT AS I TRAINED,
THE AGING OF MY FLESH

238
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:38,639
BECAME PAINFULLY CLEAR TO ME.

239
00:10:38,705 --> 00:10:44,144
HAMON PROVIDES ONLY A SMALL
ADVANTAGE OVER ORDINARY PEOPLE.

240
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:47,080
IT CANNOT GUARD
AGAINST THE PROCESS OF AGING.

241
00:10:47,147 --> 00:10:50,083
IN THE BATTLE WE FOUGHT
SO MANY YEARS AGO,

242
00:10:50,150 --> 00:10:52,653
I SECRETLY ADMIRED DIO.

243
00:10:52,719 --> 00:10:54,921
HE WAS POWERFUL.

244
00:10:54,988 --> 00:10:56,056
HE WAS BEAUTIFUL.

245
00:10:56,122 --> 00:10:59,325
HE WAS IMMORTAL.

246
00:10:59,425 --> 00:11:02,603
I COVETED THE POWER
GRANTED BY THE STONE MASK.

247
00:11:02,669 --> 00:11:05,506
I DIDN'T CARE
WHO GOT IN THE WAY.

248
00:11:05,606 --> 00:11:06,507
( Speedwagon gasps )

249
00:11:06,573 --> 00:11:10,276
YOU'RE A TWISTED TRAITOR,
STRAIZO.

250
00:11:10,343 --> 00:11:14,147
Straizo: YOUR BLOOD
WILL NOW BRING ME IMMORTALITY.

251
00:11:14,180 --> 00:11:17,851
WITH YOU GONE, THE ONLY ONES
TO KNOW OF THE MASK

252
00:11:17,951 --> 00:11:20,320
WILL BE ERINA
AND JOSEPH JOESTAR,

253
00:11:20,353 --> 00:11:22,589
AND ONCE I HAVE
DISPOSED OF THEM,

254
00:11:22,656 --> 00:11:26,326
I SHALL LEARN MORE OF THE MASK
THAN DIO EVER COULD.

255
00:11:26,359 --> 00:11:28,695
Speedwagon: NO, DON'T DO IT.

256
00:11:28,795 --> 00:11:30,130
THE KNOWLEDGE YOU'RE SEEKING

257
00:11:30,196 --> 00:11:31,932
COULD HAVE
TERRIBLE CONSEQUENCES.

258
00:11:31,998 --> 00:11:33,600
( Straizo gags )

259
00:11:33,667 --> 00:11:34,868
( screams )

260
00:11:34,968 --> 00:11:37,370
Speedwagon: JO...JO.

261
00:11:37,437 --> 00:11:40,306
ERINA...

262
00:11:41,775 --> 00:11:44,144
( Straizo gurgling )

263
00:11:48,882 --> 00:11:51,317
( tires squeal )

264
00:11:52,719 --> 00:11:55,121
Driver: HEY, YOU!
WHY DON'T YA GET A CLUE

265
00:11:55,188 --> 00:11:56,322
WHAT YOU'RE DOIN', DUMB‐ASS?

266
00:11:56,389 --> 00:11:57,991
PULL YOUR HEAD OUT OF YOUR BUTT,

267
00:11:58,058 --> 00:11:59,125
AND SEE WHERE YOU ARE!

268
00:11:59,192 --> 00:12:01,635
NOW GET THE HELL OUT OF MY WAY!

269
00:12:01,702 --> 00:12:02,703
( grunts )

270
00:12:02,736 --> 00:12:04,237
JoJo: HELLO THERE.

271
00:12:04,304 --> 00:12:07,307
WHAT? DIDN'T HEAR THAT.
I CAN'T MAKE IT OUT.

272
00:12:07,373 --> 00:12:09,242
WOULD YOU MIND
REPEATING ALL THAT?

273
00:12:09,309 --> 00:12:12,012
I'D LIKE TO KNOW WHAT IT WAS
YOU MEANT TO SAY,

274
00:12:12,078 --> 00:12:14,314
IN CASE I HAVE TO POUND YOU.

275
00:12:14,380 --> 00:12:15,749
‐ ( driver gasps )
‐ Erina: JOJO.

276
00:12:15,849 --> 00:12:17,017
( JoJo gasps )

277
00:12:17,083 --> 00:12:18,719
Erina: WHAT IS IT
YOU'RE DOING THERE?

278
00:12:18,752 --> 00:12:20,253
JoJo: UH, GRANNY ERINA.

279
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:22,923
Erina: I ASKED WHAT
YOU'RE DOING WITH THAT MAN.

280
00:12:22,989 --> 00:12:25,559
JoJo: UH, WELL, YOU SEE...

281
00:12:25,592 --> 00:12:27,060
THIS MAN IS...

282
00:12:27,093 --> 00:12:28,562
( gasps )

283
00:12:28,595 --> 00:12:29,763
A TAXI!

284
00:12:29,863 --> 00:12:32,766
THIS WAY,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO WALK SO FAR.

285
00:12:32,866 --> 00:12:35,769
Erina: THANK YOU, JOJO.
YOU'RE SUCH A THOUGHTFUL BOY.

286
00:12:35,869 --> 00:12:38,739
CLIMB IN, SMOKEY.
WE'RE GOING FOR A RIDE.

287
00:12:38,772 --> 00:12:40,774
♪

288
00:12:40,841 --> 00:12:42,442
Smokey: THE JOESTAR FAMILY,

289
00:12:42,509 --> 00:12:46,246
REDUCED TO A GRANDMOTHER
AND HER GRANDSON.

290
00:12:47,447 --> 00:12:51,685
OVER TIME, I WOULD HEAR
BITS OF THEIR PAST.

291
00:12:51,752 --> 00:12:53,053
JoJo: GRANNY, REALLY.

292
00:12:53,119 --> 00:12:54,555
SPEEDWAGON SENT FOR US,

293
00:12:54,621 --> 00:12:57,123
AND WE CAME
ALL THE WAY TO NEW YORK

294
00:12:57,190 --> 00:12:58,291
SIMPLY BECAUSE HE ASKED,

295
00:12:58,391 --> 00:13:00,527
BUT NOW WE FIND
HE'S NOT EVEN HERE?

296
00:13:00,594 --> 00:13:02,468
I THINK HIS BEHAVIOR
IS QUITE RUDE.

297
00:13:02,536 --> 00:13:04,404
Erina: I'M SURE
THAT THE OIL BUSINESS

298
00:13:04,470 --> 00:13:06,139
REQUIRES MUCH OF HIS TIME.

299
00:13:06,239 --> 00:13:07,574
( JoJo groans )

300
00:13:07,641 --> 00:13:09,275
HMM.

301
00:13:10,210 --> 00:13:11,812
SAY, GRANNY...

302
00:13:11,878 --> 00:13:12,813
Erina: HMM?

303
00:13:12,879 --> 00:13:14,147
JoJo: I'M CURIOUS.

304
00:13:14,214 --> 00:13:16,449
WAS SPEEDWAGON
REALLY GRANDPA'S BEST FRIEND?

305
00:13:16,482 --> 00:13:19,152
IS THAT ALL IT WAS?
COME ON NOW.

306
00:13:19,252 --> 00:13:21,121
Erina: WHAT ARE YOU IMPLYING?

307
00:13:21,154 --> 00:13:24,991
Speedwagon: WELL, LET'S SEE.
HE WAS NEVER MARRIED, WAS HE?

308
00:13:25,058 --> 00:13:26,893
AND YOU YOURSELF ARE A WIDOW.

309
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:29,730
WELL, IT LEADS ME TO WONDER
IF SIMPLE FRIENDSHIP

310
00:13:29,796 --> 00:13:33,066
WAS THE ONLY RELATIONSHIP
THAT WAS GOING ON THERE.

311
00:13:33,133 --> 00:13:34,601
( Erina scoffs )

312
00:13:34,668 --> 00:13:35,669
YOU ROGUE, YOU!

313
00:13:35,769 --> 00:13:38,238
‐ JoJo: SORRY. OW! I WAS WRONG.
‐ ( thumping )

314
00:13:38,304 --> 00:13:40,306
OW! FORGIVE ME. AAH!

315
00:13:40,340 --> 00:13:42,175
I KNOW SPEEDWAGON IS LOYAL. OW!

316
00:13:42,275 --> 00:13:43,510
AGH! OW!

317
00:13:43,577 --> 00:13:46,346
Smokey: THE JOESTARS
TENDED TO BE SHORT‐LIVED.

318
00:13:46,412 --> 00:13:50,483
GRANNY ERINA LOST HER HUSBAND
IN AN ACCIDENT AT SEA.

319
00:13:50,517 --> 00:13:53,687
SHE WAS PREGNANT
WITH A SON AT THE TIME.

320
00:13:53,754 --> 00:13:54,855
WHEN HE GREW UP,

321
00:13:54,955 --> 00:13:58,825
HE MARRIED A GIRL
WHO HAD ALSO SURVIVED THE WRECK.

322
00:13:58,859 --> 00:14:00,527
THEY WERE JOJO'S PARENTS,

323
00:14:00,594 --> 00:14:03,704
LATER CLAIMED
BY WAR AND DISEASE.

324
00:14:05,171 --> 00:14:08,141
GRANNY ERINA WAS
A GENTLE AND GIVING WOMAN,

325
00:14:08,208 --> 00:14:11,477
EVEN TO PUNKS LIKE ME
OR ANYBODY ELSE.

326
00:14:11,545 --> 00:14:15,716
MAYBE IT WAS BECAUSE
SHE LIVED WITH LONELINESS.

327
00:14:15,816 --> 00:14:17,618
JOJO WAS THE SAME.

328
00:14:17,684 --> 00:14:22,523
THIS TIME, HOWEVER, HIS BASIC
KINDNESS GOT HIM INTO TROUBLE...

329
00:14:22,556 --> 00:14:23,724
( overlapping chatter )

330
00:14:23,790 --> 00:14:24,858
...THANKS TO ME.

331
00:14:24,891 --> 00:14:26,893
Man: HEY, WAITER. WAITER!

332
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:28,128
Waiter: YES, SIR?

333
00:14:28,194 --> 00:14:30,363
Man: WHO DECIDED
THAT STINKIN' ANIMAL

334
00:14:30,396 --> 00:14:32,666
COULD BE ALLOWED IN HERE, HUH?

335
00:14:32,733 --> 00:14:33,867
HUH?!

336
00:14:33,900 --> 00:14:35,401
♪

337
00:14:35,468 --> 00:14:37,704
HIS SMELL
IS RUININ' MY APPETITE.

338
00:14:37,738 --> 00:14:40,406
THAT KIND SHOULDN'T BE ALLOWED
IN A PLACE LIKE THIS.

339
00:14:40,473 --> 00:14:41,742
Waiter: I UNDERSTAND, SIR,

340
00:14:41,808 --> 00:14:44,377
BUT THERE IS A POLICY
HANDED DOWN BY MANAGEMENT.

341
00:14:44,410 --> 00:14:47,180
AS LONG AS THE CHECK
IS PAID IN FULL,

342
00:14:47,247 --> 00:14:48,381
WE HAPPILY SERVE ANYONE.

343
00:14:48,414 --> 00:14:49,550
Man: WHAT WAS THAT?

344
00:14:49,583 --> 00:14:51,518
YOU'LL HAPPILY
LET BEASTS LIKE THAT

345
00:14:51,585 --> 00:14:53,520
DO THEIR GRAZING IN HERE? HUH?

346
00:14:53,587 --> 00:14:56,590
Smokey: UH, GUESS I'LL
JUST BE ON MY WAY.

347
00:14:57,891 --> 00:15:00,601
( JoJo growls )

348
00:15:00,701 --> 00:15:01,568
Erina: JOJO.

349
00:15:01,602 --> 00:15:03,537
JoJo: YOU HEARD HIM. COME ON.

350
00:15:03,604 --> 00:15:06,740
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO TELL ME
TO STOP, ARE YOU?

351
00:15:06,773 --> 00:15:09,943
Erina: NO. PEOPLE ARE
ENTITLED TO THEIR OPINIONS.

352
00:15:10,043 --> 00:15:11,745
BUT THIS MISBEGOTTEN OAF

353
00:15:11,778 --> 00:15:14,347
HAS GIVEN PUBLIC INSULT
TO OUR FRIEND.

354
00:15:14,414 --> 00:15:16,349
BE MINDFUL
OF THE OTHER GUESTS NOW,

355
00:15:16,416 --> 00:15:18,351
BUT TEACH HIM A LESSON.

356
00:15:19,352 --> 00:15:21,121
Man #2: HMM.

357
00:15:21,221 --> 00:15:23,456
JoJo: I WAS HOPING
YOU'D SAY THAT.

358
00:15:23,524 --> 00:15:25,892
( man #1 laughs )

359
00:15:25,959 --> 00:15:29,029
WELL, NOW, BOY,
LOOKIN' TO FIGHT?

360
00:15:29,095 --> 00:15:30,030
( knuckles crack )

361
00:15:31,464 --> 00:15:32,899
JoJo: LET ME HELP.

362
00:15:32,966 --> 00:15:34,968
IF THE BRASS KNUCKLES
ARE WHAT YOU'RE LOOKING FOR,

363
00:15:35,068 --> 00:15:37,704
YOU ARE NOT GOING TO FIND THEM
INSIDE OF YOUR COAT.

364
00:15:37,771 --> 00:15:40,807
YOU MIGHT WANT TO CHECK
YOUR BACK POCKET INSTEAD.

365
00:15:40,907 --> 00:15:41,742
Man #1: WHA?

366
00:15:41,808 --> 00:15:43,910
‐ ( diners murmur)
‐ Smokey: WHAT?

367
00:15:46,446 --> 00:15:49,282
Man #1: EH? NO WAY.

368
00:15:49,315 --> 00:15:50,483
EH?

369
00:15:50,584 --> 00:15:51,985
JoJo: NEXT YOU'LL SAY,
"YOU BASTARD,

370
00:15:52,085 --> 00:15:54,655
HOW COULD YOU HAVE POSSIBLY
KNOWN WHERE THEY WERE?"

371
00:15:54,721 --> 00:15:56,256
Man #1: YOU BASTARD,
HOW COULD YOU

372
00:15:56,322 --> 00:15:57,658
POSSIBLY HAVE KNOWN
WHERE THEY WERE?

373
00:15:57,724 --> 00:15:58,959
HUH?!

374
00:15:58,992 --> 00:16:01,301
JoJo: BY THE VISIBLE ABRASIONS

375
00:16:01,334 --> 00:16:03,770
THAT ARE ON YOUR RIGHT HAND,
IT'S OBVIOUS

376
00:16:03,837 --> 00:16:06,507
THAT YOU DO YOUR FIGHTING
USING BRASS KNUCKLES.

377
00:16:06,607 --> 00:16:07,841
YOU'VE NO WOUNDS,

378
00:16:07,908 --> 00:16:10,176
SO THE THE BLOOD ON YOUR SHIRT
IS NOT FROM YOU.

379
00:16:10,276 --> 00:16:11,177
‐ ( man #1 yells )
‐ JoJo: THEREFORE,

380
00:16:11,277 --> 00:16:12,813
YOU'VE JUST COME FROM A FIGHT.

381
00:16:12,846 --> 00:16:14,681
SINCE THE BLOOD
IS ON YOUR SHIRT

382
00:16:14,748 --> 00:16:16,850
AND NOT THAT PINK HORROR
OF A COAT,

383
00:16:16,917 --> 00:16:19,686
IT WAS TAKEN OFF
PRIOR TO THE FIGHT.

384
00:16:19,786 --> 00:16:22,255
AND THEN AFTER YOU
HAD COMPLETED YOUR ASSAULT,

385
00:16:22,322 --> 00:16:25,358
THE KNUCKLES CAME OFF,
AND THAT'S WHEN YOU PROCEEDED

386
00:16:25,425 --> 00:16:28,161
TO STOW THEM AWAY
IN YOUR BACK POCKET.

387
00:16:28,194 --> 00:16:29,362
( man #1 growls )

388
00:16:30,496 --> 00:16:32,633
JoJo: FOR MY NEXT GLIMPSE
INTO THE FUTURE,

389
00:16:32,699 --> 00:16:35,335
YOU WILL NOW SAY,
"SO WHAT, YOU LITTLE PUNK?"

390
00:16:35,368 --> 00:16:37,270
Man #1: YEAH, SO WHAT,
YOU LITTLE PUNK?

391
00:16:37,337 --> 00:16:39,205
AND NOW YOU'RE GONNA GET IT.

392
00:16:39,305 --> 00:16:41,207
I GOT YA!

393
00:16:41,307 --> 00:16:44,845
( grunting )

394
00:16:44,878 --> 00:16:46,212
YOU LIKE THAT, HUH?

395
00:16:46,279 --> 00:16:48,048
THAT'LL TEACH YOU A LESSON.

396
00:16:48,114 --> 00:16:50,150
JoJo: SORRY. YOU MISSED.

397
00:16:50,216 --> 00:16:52,886
WHAT HAVE YOU BEEN PUNCHING?

398
00:16:52,953 --> 00:16:56,557
I WASN'T THE ONE
YOU WERE PUMMELING SO HAPPILY.

399
00:16:56,623 --> 00:16:58,124
Man #1: OH, MY GOD!

400
00:16:58,191 --> 00:16:59,560
( groans )

401
00:16:59,626 --> 00:17:01,067
JoJo: I CAN PREDICT AND COUNTER

402
00:17:01,134 --> 00:17:03,737
ANYTHING YOUR TINY BRAIN
IS ABLE TO COME UP WITH.

403
00:17:03,804 --> 00:17:06,139
DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT NOW,
YOU SIMPLETON?

404
00:17:06,206 --> 00:17:09,075
( crowd laughs )

405
00:17:14,380 --> 00:17:16,249
Man #2: PLEASE,
FORGIVE THE BEHAVIOR

406
00:17:16,316 --> 00:17:17,483
OF MY UNDERLING, MADAM.

407
00:17:17,551 --> 00:17:21,487
YOU'RE ERINA JOESTAR,
AREN'T YOU?

408
00:17:21,555 --> 00:17:23,590
I'VE WORKED ON A LOT
OF BUSINESS DEALS

409
00:17:23,690 --> 00:17:25,358
WITH YOUR MR. SPEEDWAGON,
YOU SEE.

410
00:17:25,425 --> 00:17:27,528
HE TOLD ME SOME STORIES
ABOUT YOU

411
00:17:27,594 --> 00:17:30,063
WHEN HIM AND ME WERE IN LONDON
A WHILE BACK.

412
00:17:30,096 --> 00:17:31,197
I'M GLAD TO MEET YOU.

413
00:17:31,264 --> 00:17:34,601
I HEARD A LITTLE SOMETHING
THROUGH THE GRAPEVINE.

414
00:17:34,668 --> 00:17:37,337
IT HASN'T MADE IT
INTO THE PAPERS YET,

415
00:17:37,403 --> 00:17:38,672
BUT YOU SHOULD KNOW.

416
00:17:39,873 --> 00:17:43,109
IT SEEMS THAT MR. SPEEDWAGON
HAS BEEN MURDERED.

417
00:17:43,209 --> 00:17:44,511
( both gasp )

418
00:17:44,578 --> 00:17:45,879
JoJo: ARE YOU SURE?

419
00:17:45,946 --> 00:17:48,615
Man #2: RUMOR IS
THE CAT WHO DID IT

420
00:17:48,715 --> 00:17:50,617
WAS SOME SORT
OF TIBETAN MONK.

421
00:17:50,684 --> 00:17:53,453
JoJo: SOME SORT OF MONK?
COULD IT BE STRAIZO?

422
00:17:53,554 --> 00:17:56,590
Man #2: ALL THEY'RE SAYING IS
THAT THE BODIES OF SPEEDWAGON

423
00:17:56,623 --> 00:17:59,259
AND HIS TEAM WASHED UP
ALONG A RIVERBANK

424
00:17:59,292 --> 00:18:00,567
SOMEWHERE DOWN IN MEXICO.

425
00:18:00,634 --> 00:18:02,903
IT'S A GENUINE MYSTERY.

426
00:18:02,969 --> 00:18:05,038
NOBODY HAS ANY IDEA
WHY THEY WERE KILLED

427
00:18:05,105 --> 00:18:07,741
OR WHERE THE MONK
MIGHT HAVE GONE TO AFTERWARD.

428
00:18:07,808 --> 00:18:08,942
( JoJo and Erina gasp )

429
00:18:08,975 --> 00:18:12,478
Erina: ACTUALLY,
I THINK I MIGHT KNOW.

430
00:18:12,579 --> 00:18:14,480
PERHAPS.

431
00:18:14,548 --> 00:18:18,151
SPEEDWAGON SAID SOMETHING
A LONG TIME AGO.

432
00:18:18,251 --> 00:18:19,620
IT INVOLVED DIO

433
00:18:19,653 --> 00:18:22,923
AND THE HORRIBLE STONE MASK
THAT CHANGED HIM.

434
00:18:22,989 --> 00:18:25,592
Smokey: JOJO,
THAT GUY IS A MAFIA MAN.

435
00:18:25,659 --> 00:18:27,828
YOU CAN'T TRUST
WHAT HE TELLS YOU.

436
00:18:27,894 --> 00:18:29,663
HE'S TRYING TO PULL SOMETHING!

437
00:18:29,730 --> 00:18:32,599
Man #2: BELIEVE WHATEVER
YOU WANT TO, KID.

438
00:18:32,666 --> 00:18:34,267
JoJo: HOLD ON.

439
00:18:34,334 --> 00:18:35,802
TRY YOUR BREAST POCKET

440
00:18:35,836 --> 00:18:37,804
‐ IF YOU'RE AFTER YOUR LIGHTER.
‐ Man #2: EH?

441
00:18:37,838 --> 00:18:40,774
JoJo: ANYWAY,
THANKS FOR THE WARNING, SMOKEY.

442
00:18:40,841 --> 00:18:44,511
BUT I THINK I BELIEVE
WHAT THIS MAN IS TELLING US.

443
00:18:44,578 --> 00:18:47,013
THESE FELLOWS ARE ONLY
MOTIVATED BY MONEY.

444
00:18:47,113 --> 00:18:50,584
CLEARLY INFORMATION LIKE THAT
IS VALUABLE TO HIS ORGANIZATION,

445
00:18:50,651 --> 00:18:53,019
SO I'M INCLINED
TO LISTEN TO HIM.

446
00:18:53,119 --> 00:18:54,087
HOWEVER...

447
00:18:54,154 --> 00:18:56,523
( man #2 groaning )

448
00:18:56,623 --> 00:19:01,034
JoJo: AS TRUE AS THAT MAY BE,
YOU DON'T SIMPLY WALTZ OVER HERE

449
00:19:01,101 --> 00:19:04,304
AND THEN JUST BLURT OUT
AWFUL NEWS TO GRANNY ERINA.

450
00:19:04,370 --> 00:19:07,774
DON'T YOU SEE HOW BADLY UPSET
YOU'VE MADE HER WITH THIS NEWS?

451
00:19:07,841 --> 00:19:09,510
YOU ARE VERY THOUGHTLESS!

452
00:19:09,543 --> 00:19:11,545
( man #2 yelps )

453
00:19:11,645 --> 00:19:14,715
Erina: IT WAS 50 YEARS AGO,

454
00:19:14,815 --> 00:19:18,619
AND STILL THOSE EVENTS HAUNT US.

455
00:19:18,685 --> 00:19:21,187
JoJo: DON'T BE FRIGHTENED.
I'M HERE,

456
00:19:21,221 --> 00:19:22,656
AND I'LL PROTECT YOU.

457
00:19:22,723 --> 00:19:24,357
Erina: YOU MUSTN'T, JOSEPH.

458
00:19:24,390 --> 00:19:26,059
I'M CONCERNED FOR YOU.

459
00:19:26,159 --> 00:19:30,296
I DON'T WANT YOU SNARED BY EVIL
FROM A HALF‐CENTURY AGO.

460
00:19:30,363 --> 00:19:32,032
JoJo: I'LL BE FINE, GRANNY.

461
00:19:33,199 --> 00:19:37,871
IF THIS IS MY FATE,
I ACCEPT IT FULLY.

462
00:19:37,904 --> 00:19:39,640
♪

463
00:19:39,706 --> 00:19:41,074
Smokey: AT THE TIME,

464
00:19:41,141 --> 00:19:43,910
I DIDN'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT WAS GOING ON,

465
